      "comment": "LITTLE DITZY (2) was well supported last time but could only manage third (22.75), beaten 2.5 lengths. Well-placed to take this out. PERPETUUS (1) had a tricky draw but scored by 0.8 lengths (22.99) at Mandurah in Novice race. Has been out the placings in all four runs here. Will go close again if runs up to latest. KAKEGURUI (8) was safely held in tougher company last start after settling off pace at Mandurah, but prior to that won by 2.25 lengths at this track (16.15) beating Phoebe Keeping in a Grade 6 on April 22. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. RIPPIN' PIKE (4) cannot be left out despite coming off a short break.",
